Feb 26 2007	A good London base convenient and friendly!	After reading the comments on this site in January I was a little dubious about this hotel, but after staying there I have to say I was pleasantly surprised. For a four star hotel, I got a very reasonable rate and was impressed particularly with the check-in staff, the room, and the food in the restaurant. Both dinner and breakfast were excellent, and there are spectacular views from the restaurant. If you don't want to eat in the restaurant then there is a Pizza Express right outside and many other eateries within easy reach.If you are looking for architecture and splendour, go elsewhere. This is a functional hotel in an office-style building (the hotel is on the ninth floor upwards), but it is very well-located, with updated modern rooms and excellent amenities. My mum and I were seeing a show at the Palladium and it was literally a five minute walk, and even less walking time to Regent Street and shopping.Additionally, it was very quiet due to the fact that the rooms are not at street level, and if you like ventilation you can open the windows and not be deafened by street noise. The elevators were a little noisy at times, but not enough to keep us awake. As a hotellier's daughter, I can honestly say that compared to the many hotels I've stayed in, including many in London in this range, this was one of our most enjoyable stays. If you want to stay in London but are perhaps less concerned with aesthetics and more concerned with a nice room and comfy bed with great views and location, then this is worth a try. I would definitely stay at the Saint Georges again.	
