Nov 12 2005 	Loved the St. Georges	I agree with the other review re the lobby being small and the hallways rather dull. -- However, my room was very comfortable and it had an amazing view of the city. I usually ate breakfast and dinner at the hotel and the food was much better than I had expected it to be. When I chose to eat in my room, room service was very fast and efficient. -- I loved the restaurant. I would often go up in the evening just to look out on the skyline. -- The only drawback for me is that I am allergic to smoke and would leave when there were a lot of smokers present. -- I found the hotel staff and the restaurant staff helpful and pleasant. -- I would stay there again.	
Oct 15 2005	Terrible hotel -- noisy rude overpriced	Don't be fooled by the &quot;four stars&quot; with the St. Georges. The rooms are quite stale and lackluster for the hundeds of dollars you'll pay. Worse, a thunderous elevator rattles through the walls of several suites (the shaft is next to rooms on every floor). When we asked for a change of rooms due to this infernal noise, the staff was dismissive and utterly unhelpful. For the price we were paying, it seems a crime to have such poor accommodations and service. To make matters worse, the hotel fails to inform guests that they *charge* for their continental breakfast -- a whopping 11 pounds ($20) per person, surprising you on your checkout bill. Not even the lowest class hotels we patronised charged their guests for continental breakfast. The least they could do is put a little sign up or inform guests of their unorthodox policy.I could go on, but why beat a dead horse?We will never stay at the St. Georges again. Ever. One gets the sense that this hotel survives simply because it's right next door to the BBC headquarters, and they can charge ridiculously high rates for BBC guests. Or something.Why anyone would ever come to this hotel is a mystery to me. My advice: for your money, try the Barkston Gardens in Earls Court. Same hotel chain, but a lot friendlier, quieter, and far less money. And complimentary breakfast, of course.	
Oct 13 2005	It was actually great	I booked this hotel and found this review side only later, and must admit, I got scared. But... suprise, suprise, I really liked the Saint Georges Hotel. For a London Hotel, it was excellent, London hotels are usually lousy, no matter how many stars they have, but this was a nice change from that. Clean room, impeccable bathroom, friendly staff. From arriving to leaving, everything went smooth. The breakfast was good, with a great view over London from the 15th floor. I stayed in other Hotels in London before, and this was by far the best. I recommend it to everyone who made bad experiences with other London hotels.	
